When polling weather data:

- Process each city independently.
- A failure for one city must not stop polling of other cities.
- Log city name, exception type, HTTP status if available, and retry count at WARNING level.
- Retry weather API requests at most 3 times.
- Do not raise exceptions after final retry.
- A reading must only be stored when its timestamp differs from the latest stored timestamp for that city.
- Invalid API responses must not overwrite previously stored valid readings.